      • getSubCNF

        public CNF getSubCNF(String variable)
        Filters all disjunctions that could be evaluated with the given variable and returns them in a new CNF Example: Given myFilter = CNF((a = b) And (b > 5 OR a > 10) AND (c = false) AND (a = c)) myFilter.getSubCNF(a,b) => CNF((a = b) And (b > 5 OR a > 10))
        Parameters:
        variable - variable that must be included in the disjunction
        Returns:
        CNF containing only the specified variable

      • getSubCNF

        public CNF getSubCNF(Set<String> variables)
        Filters all disjunctions that could be evaluated with the given set of variables and returns them in a new CNF Example: Given myFilter = CNF((a = b) And (b > 5 OR a > 10) AND (c = false) AND (a = c)) myFilter.getSubCNF(a,b) => CNF((a = b) And (b > 5 OR a > 10))
        Parameters:
        variables - set of variables that must be included in the disjunction
        Returns:
        CNF containing only variables covered by the input list

      • removeSubCNF

        public CNF removeSubCNF(String variable)
        Filters all disjunctions that could be evaluated with the given variable and removes them from the CNF. The filtered predicates will be returned in a new CNF Example: Given myFilter = CNF((a = 10) AND (b > 5 OR a > 10) AND (c = false) AND (a = c)) myFilter.removeSubCNF(a) => CNF(a = 10) and myFilter == CNF((b > 5 OR a > 10) AND (c = false) AND (a = c))
        Parameters:
        variable - variable that must be included in the disjunction
        Returns:
        CNF containing only variables covered by the input list

      • removeSubCNF

        public CNF removeSubCNF(Set<String> variables)
        Filters all disjunctions that could be evaluated with the given set of variables and removes them from the CNF. The filtered predicates will be returned in a new CNF Example: Given myFilter = CNF((a = b) AND (b > 5 OR a > 10) AND (c = false) AND (a = c)) myFilter.removeSubCNF(a,b) => CNF((a = b) And (b > 5 OR a > 10)) and myFilter == CNF((c = false) AND (a = c))
        Parameters:
        variables - set of variables that must be included in the disjunction
        Returns:
        CNF containing only variables covered by the input list
